rrent debates regarding the politics of publishing of ethnic writers, examining how Kunzru has managed to shape a career in resistance of narrow labelling where many other writers have struggled to achieve long-term recognition.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aBritish.  aContemporary.  aCosmopolitan.  aGlobal.  aKunzru.  aLiterature.  aNovel.  aPostcolonial.  aPostmodern.  aTwenty-first century.1 aDot, Maëlle Jeanniard du, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEly, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHering, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLoh, Lucienne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMahn, Churnjeet, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNicol, Bran, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShaw, Kristian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShaw, Kristian, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aUpstone, Sara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aUpstone, Sara, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152615521440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526155214423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526155214/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles